Save this! I wanted to share a gym workout with you! This is a new gym we are visiting and considering joining.

Ever since we moved in April, working out has been tough. Historically, I workout way more consistently in a gym environment than I do a home environment, but we live about 25 minutes away from even small gyms in our area.

Nonetheless, I wanted to start back working out in a gym at least a few days a week. Today’s video is a back workout. I’m performing 4 sets of 12 reps with 30-45 seconds of rest in between before moving onto the next movement.

If you try this, be sure that your weight is such that you are really having to push through the last 2-3 reps. If you can get through all 12 with ease, it’s time to increase the amount of weight you are using!

Here are the movements I did:
-Seated cable row
-Lat pushdown/supermans
-Lat pulldown
-Bent over row

This workout is very similar to the workouts you’ll see in week one of my upcoming New Year’s challenge! There are both home workouts and gym workouts and they are developed to get you in and out and on your way.

We want to grow pretty, lean muscle because, in doing so, we will actually increase our RMR which is our resting metabolic rate. So often we see women whose metabolism isn’t where it should be, and this is one piece of the puzzle to helping you lose weight and keep it off for life.

Here’s a quick breakfast idea for if you are short on time or aren’t skilled at cooking!

Do I prefer a breakfast like this over a home cooked meal? Nope! But is this sometimes reality? Yup!

This breakfast fits perfectly into my balanced plan, and fits into my low-carb plan as long as you watch your carbs closely for the rest of the day. 19 total grams of carbs in one metal is a bit high for low-carb, but if you make adjustments to your remaining meals of the day you are good to go!

I want to make a note about these tortillas…I like them because they taste good and their calorie count is much lower than traditional tortillas. However…they falsify their calorie count to make them appear healthier than they are.

These tortillas claim they are 45 calories. If you do the math (based on the macros) you will find they are actually 89 calories. What the company did is deduct the calories of the fiber do to a “net calorie”….but fiber calories are still calories! They should not be deducted!

Even at 89 calories, this tortilla comes in about half of the calories of many competitors which is why it was my choice!

LIZ JUST HIT 100 POUNDS LOST WITH WEIGHTLOSSHERO! This is so exciting!

Liz joined my very first New Year’s challenge in 2021. She is actually one of the reasons I continue to do challenges today. Her life changed because of one single decision to take the leap.  When she started the first challenge she was:
-a full-blown diabetic
-was maxed out on insulin
-took 5 prescription drugs, daily, for diabetes and cholesterol
-her A1C was 9.1
-she is a powerful attorney and would come home from work and just collapse from exhaustion and need to nap
-she struggled to even really WANT to change…until something clicked!

She crushed the challenge! She loved it! She was feeling better than ever. She lost weight and her blood sugar was more controlled.  Liz, also, has been coaching with our team 1:1 and, currently, meets with Hubby Heath each week!

Now Liz is:
-down 100 pounds
-her A1C went from 9.1 to 5.1
-she is no longer considered diabetic
-she is off all her meds
-she no longer needs naps after work
-she is active and loves to move!

While we think Liz is exceptional, she is no exception…anyone can see results like Liz if you take the leap and put forth the effort. Weight loss is easier than you think…and we are here to help!

Our next challenge starts on 1/9/23. Let’s make this your year to look back and say…”I finally did it”.

#builtreadymarriage

We took this picture as we were getting into the car to pick up 2 (of 4) foster children 4 hours away. Halfway there we got a call that said: turn around. 
 The kids’ foster mom was telling us one thing and telling CPS something different. She had asked us to come a day early…and she told CPS she hadn’t talked to us at ALL. She edited texts from us to make it look like we were lying.

Their foster mom had a sudden desire to keep ONE of the 4 kids. Her decision to keep them came shortly after finding out she would be getting a significant pay increase because they were leveled-up based on behavior challenges and health issues. When she described these kids to us it’s like she didn’t like them at ALL. She had no photos of them to send to us. She told us she doesn't allow them around her own two children. She allows them unfiltered access to the internet and is aware that they are watching explicit videos and does nothing to prevent it. She is mostly uninvolved in their education. 

Does this sound like a mother who suddenly wants to take a long-term interest in the well-being of children?! Now, instead of bringing all 4 kids together they hope to split them across 3 homes. It's EVIL and WICKED. 

I share this because I’m going to keep running my big mouth to anyone that will listen, we want to inspire change, and we hope to educate you on being part of the solution. We need to take MASSIVE action to help children who are not seen/heard by most.   But, also, because the Lord has been SO kind in this process. This stuff is hard! It’s an emotional tug-of-war. One moment you are planning your life with new children and then next moment you are undoing all of those plans! The beds we thought would be full are empty! The plans that we have made are no more!  But…God is in every single detail. He flooded us with peace of mind and a firm conviction that His will governs ALL! He didn’t mis-manage this and I trust that with every fiber of my soul. I don’t know what He has for us, or for those kids, but I know that His plans are GOOD for those who love Him and are faithful to him. I can’t wait to keep sharing the story that He is writing with you all.

Happy Valentine’s Day, my love. I’m so excited to start our new adventure by adding our 4 news kiddos to our family tomorrow! I thank God for you today (and every other day). Thank you for loving me and leading me so well! I love you! @heathevans44

4 big hearts
40 little fingers
40 little toes

We have 4 new members of the Evans’ family. They may be foster kids, to the world, but we already love them like they are our own. They don’t share our last name (yet), but we pray that one day they will! 

The idea of taking 4 kids on at one time felt like an overwhelming task…especially for me, because I haven’t had the joy of raising young children, until now. But this past week has been such a beautiful example of the Lord’s faithfulness to His people…even in things that seem challenging.

There is a verse that says ‘in our weakness, He is strong’, and, boy, I’m glad that is true. The Lord has already shown Himself SO strong in the last week of bringing these children into our home. There has been laughter, there have been tears, and there has been so much joy amidst painfully difficult circumstances.

The kiddos are: 9 (boy), 6 (boy), 5 (boy), and 4 (girl). To keep them safe we aren’t allowed to share specific information about them, including any name or  photos of their faces that could reveal their identity. We are going to learn creative ways to share our lives with you until the day that we can FULLY share them with you.

Here’s how you can pray:
-Pray for the kids that the Lord will heal their heartaches and will help them grow
-Pray for us, as parents, that we will surrender ourselves daily to the Lord (we know when we do that…He will take care of the rest)
-Pray for this weekend when our oldest two (Ava & Naomi who are 18 & 16) will come back to Texas for a month and will meet their new foster siblings in-person (they live in California every other month with their Mom!)
-Pray that the court system will act in the best interest of the children over the next few months
-Pray for patience for ALL as we adjust to our new lives as a family

I love you all and am so thankful that you are here on this crazy ride with our family. Now let’s see how to learn to juggle this new lifestyle keeping healthy and active!

This is 35 ❤️

5 years ago I spent my birthday throwing a party for myself at the top of a high-rise in Dallas. I had no dream or desire in my heart to be a wife or a mother…but God.

5 years later I have a new heart and that new heart has new desires (Psalm 37:4). I now have 7 hearts to love and serve and couldn’t imagine a life without each one of them.

It’s a beautiful thing to look back and see how God used it all…my ups and my downs…to bring me to a place I couldn’t have imagined. (Ephesians 3:20).

I love Jesus. I love my husband. I love my family. I love my community here. I’m thankful for the 35 years I’ve been given and can’t wait to see what the future holds.

(Also, we cannot share photos of our foster-to-adopt kiddos, which is why we faced away for this family shot to share with you all ❤️.)

Well-intended people will, often, discourage you with their ‘warnings’ of the struggles they have personally experienced.  I have experienced this in my weight-loss journey, in my journey of owning a business, and now as a foster-mom.  Here’s the truth: there are always ups and downs to everything. There is a honeymoon phase to…everything…and when the tough gets going it gives us an opportunity to turn our eyes upon Jesus even more and experience His strength in our weakness.  We’ve now had these kiddos over a month! We love them dearly! We are proud of every one of them. All things considered, they are doing SO FREAKING WELL!  They love to memorize Bible verses and sing worship songs! They love to shoot Heath with nerf guns and climb all over him! They love to jump in our freezing cold pool and can’t wait for Summer!  Are there hard moments? Yes. Will there be harder moments? Most likely. But we serve a God who gives us the strength to endure any and everything He sends our way and we rest in THAT!

Just start, just start, just start.

In my years as a weight-loss coach, I’ve always found that this is the hardest part. Most of us know what we SHOULD do…but doing it is a whole other story.

Here’s what I’ve found: action cures fear. 

Small steps in the right direction give you an internal motivation to keep going.

One minute you’re committing to a daily walk…and then you start cleaning up your food choices.

You don’t need to know everything to start…but you should seek to learn as much as you can as you go.

That’s where coaching comes in.

My team and I have helped thousands of women over the last 5 years find their healthy ending.

We do that by giving you a fool-proof plan that address the WHOLE woman, setting a fire under your rear, and holding you accountable to being who you said you would be.

If that sounds like something you need…DM me the word COACH and we will see if we are a good fit to work together.

If you aren’t there yet…start small…start scared…but just START.

Don’t let your feelings run your life! This was a HUGE issue for me in my weight-loss journey.

Feelings are real experiences in our minds, but we don’t have to submit to them.

As believers, we are supposed to submit to God’s Word in everything…even when that doesn’t necessarily align with how we FEEL in the moment.

I didn’t particularly FEEL like waking up early and cooking breakfast for my kids…but I knew it was the RIGHT thing to do. So, sure as shootin’, at my 5:55am alarm I hit my snooze once and got up and did my motherly duty unto the Lord.

If you find your feelings feel really big…pray. Surrender them to Jesus. Read God’s word. MEMORIZE God’s Word.

Most importantly, resolve that you will not lean into your feelings, but will lean into truth, instead. ❤️

Not all heroes wear capes…but they, sometimes, do. ❤️

These are my boys before a hero-themed Mother-Son dance. They were SO crazy excited to get to go on a special date with Mom, and I hope that excitement never ends.

When we got to the dance, I was a bit taken aback by the set up. I’m not sure what I was expecting from a dance geared for 6-10 year olds, but dirty rap music wasn’t it 😂.

We believe what we listen to matters. We do our best to guard their hearts and minds and keep them from the evil that is waiting for them at every turn. We explained that the music they were playing wasn’t appropriate and grabbed our candy and bounced.

Though we dipped in and out of the dance, we came home and turned on some praise music and made our own dance party. We laughed and giggled and had the best time.

If you could, be praying for us (and the kiddos) this week. There’s not much that I can share in regards to their custody case until after we (Lord-willing) adopt them down the road, but this week will serve to be a big week in their lives that will, no doubt, be full of highs and lows. Pray that the Lord protects them and heals their hearts as we navigate the ever-changing foster road together with all four of them. 🙏🏼

Your mindset is, most often, what is holding you back from getting healthy. I spent years being afraid to start and being even more afraid to stay where I was. I wanted to always wait until my feelings matched up with what was RIGHT and I soon realized that I would be waiting for the rest of my life.  I had to learn to just start…

Start messy…

Start afraid…

…and to stop waiting for me to FEEL like doing the hard work.  If that’s you, let me encourage you:  JUST START.  You are going to mess this up a thousand times…

Just commit to keep going with each missed step.

Your healthy life…inside and out…awaits you!

By the way, these mindsets are some of the very mindsets that I teach in Weightlosshero University and in my 1:1 and group coaching programs. When we don’t tackle what’s going on internally…the external will never be fixed. When trying to lose weight we try to fix a heart problem by modifying a few behaviors, and it’s why it never lasts.  Most diets work…most workouts work…but sticking to things long-term is where we fail. You should come join us at Weightlosshero and start doing the heart work WITH the hard work…

Comment below and let me know which of these is the biggest struggle for you?  Mine has always been consistency. I LOVE to go all in, head first, but then can tend to not stay there very long.  Often, just knowing what our pitfalls are can help us avoid them and know how to work to become better all-around.

On my last slide I shared a coaching client success story, Dawn, and forgot to add one detail: she is now down 85 pounds AND off of her blood pressure medication. What a win!  Dawn started with us as a 1:1 client, went off on her own and continued to lose using the things she learned with Weightlosshero, and now has joined our group coaching program for added accountability.  Our group coaching comes with a program called Weightlosshero University which is an educational system to teach you all of the common things I teach our 1:1 clients in private sessions.

In addition to the WLH U, you get monthly meal plans, work outs, Bible reading plans, and TWO live coaching sessions with me (weekly!) to answer your questions and coach you in the same way I coach my private clients.  We have 13 spots left in our beta group which locks you in at $100 off with code: LOYAL.  I am so excited about this coaching program and have ZERO doubt that if you join and truly submit to our way of life that you will find the results you’re looking for.

It is something to celebrate when any kids graduate from kindergarten…but I think it’s extra special when your life has been an uphill battle. This is our 6-year-old boy and he is officially moving onto first grade.

Foster children have many battles most of us will never know about. Ours have the trauma that brought them into care, the exposure to things they never should have been exposed to, moving schools, being separated from siblings for long periods of time, and being moved to multiple different homes.

Despite all of these things they are so beautifully resilient! They love to learn! They love hard and they work hard! They are fighting well and we are in the battle with them.

Little buddy…your mommy and daddy are proud of you and can’t wait to watch you continue to grow more and more 🥰

Here’s my new, updated EASY ranch recipe! Instead of using fresh ingredients, this recipe uses dried ingredients that you can keep on-hand. TRUST ME when I say this is the yummiest ranch, ever, and can bring so much flavor to anything!  Ingredients:
* 1 cup mayo
* 1/3 cup unsweetened Silk almond milk or cashew milk
* 3 tablespoons ranch powder 
* 2 tablespoons minced green onions (dried)
* 2 tablespoons chopped parsley (dried)
* 1 tablespoon ground black pepper
* 1 teaspoon apple cider vinegar
* 1 teaspoon white wine vinegar

Directions:
1. Mix almond (or cashew) milk with apple cider vinegar in a small bowl and let sit for 10 minutes. (This makes a ‘mock’ buttermilk that is dairy-free and lasts longer in the fridge!)
2. After the 10 minutes have passed, add all remaining ingredients and stir.
3. Pour into a container and store in the refrigerator. Best if consumed within 10 days.

Macros:
Serving size: 2 tbsp
130 cals - 14g Fat - 1g Protein - <1 Carb

If you’re looking for more recipe ideas, always head to my blog!

Do you struggle with how to eat as a diabetic? Do you feel low energy and blood sugar issues and even the idea of losing weight is overwhelming? Meet LIZ! She is down over 100 pounds since starting with Weightlosshero and is FREE from her fight with type II diabetes.

Liz has known Heath, personally, for forever. She was 100 pounds heavier with an A1C of 9.1. She took multiple prescription medications and every day after work (she’s a crazy awesome lawyer) she would have to lie down and rest.  Now? 100 pounds down. She’s off almost all meds. Her A1C is 5.1 (this is considered ‘normal’ and non-diabetic). She takes NO diabetes or cholesterol meds. After work she is active and doesn’t need daily naps.  Her whole life changed because of one decision to jump in and trust us. She has not been without setbacks but she has faithfully followed our plan and has seen results. She is currently, still, a 1:1 client with Coach Hubby Heath and knows she needs to continued accountability to keep doing the right things.  Liz…you already know how proud I am of you. It has been so beautiful to be able to share this journey of health with you and to see you get your life back.

You already know what I’m going to say! We are here to help! We coach women every day…it’s our joy to help women get healthy spiritually, mentally, physically, and emotionally. If you are looking for your roadmap to healthy…send me a DM with the word COACH and let’s see if you are a candidate for our accountability coaching programs. The future you will be so glad you did!!

“There is a great need to be settled because there are so many things to unsettle us.” -Thomas Watson

I think a lot of our habits of running to food begin with not being settled and being settled on the wrong things.

Before I lost 150 pounds I would face unsettling realities and food was ALWAYS my first thought. It was my god. It was the thing that I ran to in times of trouble.  Even after the Lord saved me I can find myself running to others for comfort before I run to my Heavenly Father…ya know, the ONE who holds my future 😂.

I hope that this quote provides an opportunity to ask yourself the same question that I did this week: what settles me?

My prayer is that if you find it’s anything other than Jesus that you will repent and fight to choose differently…even starting today!

We have to stop the patters of running to the wrong things and we have to decide what really settles us amidst the storms of our lives.

5 years ago I would have told you I didn’t think I ever wanted kids…

…now I have 6 of them.

5 years ago I would have told you I never wanted to be married again…

…now I’m married to my best friend and believe it’s the most wonderful gift, apart from my salvation.

See that’s what my God does!

He took my heart of stone and made it a heart of flesh!

He gave me new desires!

What was once burdensome to me is now a joy to me!!

For years I thought I was too ‘bad’ for God. I still loved my sinful ways. I wasn’t sure I was cut out to be a Christian.

But then God did what God does! He looked on me with love and saved my soul for all of eternity and turned my life around!

Do you deal with intrusive/disruptive thoughts? When they come to you struggle with how to battle them?  As my pastor said one Sunday…’when fear comes at us with ‘what if’s’…we have to respond with ‘I know’s’….

But we can’t speak the truth we don’t know. Part of taking our thoughts captive is knowing and loving the TRUTH of God’s Word! Without it there is no freedom from these thoughts…  When these thoughts run wild…what do we do? We look to calm them. We look to still them. And for many of us, it sends us running to food as a balm to a disruptive mind.  But food can never quiet your soul and it can never set you free…only Jesus can do that. We can take our thoughts captive and submit our minds to Christ but intentionally dealing with our thoughts in truthful ways and bringing them to glorify God above all.  My challenge for you is to start rehearsing truth in your mind. When doubt fills your mind…remind yourself of who God is and who He has been do you. When fear creeps in remind yourself of who is in control and that you will never face anything alone.

We can’t stop the thoughts from coming…but we don’t have to let them hold us captive, so long as we are in Christ. ❤️

You say a picture is worth 1,000 words, but I say that this one is worth 2k.  Let me explain…  Yes, I lost a LOT of weight….and have kept it off for 8 years…

I was on antidepressants…

I was selfish…

I was MISERABLE.  I lost all my weight…and then something worse happened:  I was more anxious than ever…  I was more selfish than ever…  I was more miserable than ever…  All of this running had me running to the wrong things, and not at all to Christ.  I wanted every sinful thing of this world and God gave me over to those desires…  And then He drew me to Himself.  It’s the craziest experience I can never explain how I could go from never wanting children to having 6 of them that I couldn’t imagine a life without.  That’s what Jesus does.  He sought me and He bought me.  He gave me a new heart and new desires.  I no longer want the things I used to want.  And I’ll never get over it.  If you have been running to all of the wrong things, let me invite you to run to the foot of the cross.  the Bible says that if you confess with your mouth and believe in your heart that Jesus Christ is Lord that you will be saved…  …and THAT is the only thing worth truly chasing after.  When you chase after a life of loving the Lord…the health, weight loss, and happiness you are looking for will follow so much easier.  It’s when we do it the other way around that we stay stuck in the same place.

The ‘all-or-nothing’ mindset will get you every time!! And when you live in that mentality you will most likely always feel shame over your less-than-healthy choices because you know that they will send you spiraling into unhealthy patterns.  This leads us to believe that we have to ALWAYS eat healthy and ALWAYS exercise and ALWAYS to EVERYTHING right in order to see results. You’re never going to get it all right and the sooner you resign to that fact the happier and more successful you will be on this journey.  Try this attitude on for size: ‘all…or…something’. Do you struggle with being discontent? I sure can (though, I never want to admit it)!

I can often want things MY way on MY timeline and when things don’t go how I planned I can struggle with anxiousness/fear as a result. I can struggle with never being satisfied and always wanting more…especially in this ‘never stop the hustle’ age we live in.

In my Bible study I read a quote that said “a fretful, discontented spirit is open to many temptations, and those that indulge it are in danger of doing evil”.

That statement was an eye opener for me and I wonder who out there can relate. The moment discontent starts to set in…it I don’t squash it it spreads like a wildfire.

How many times have you felt discontent with where you are in your life?

What about on your weight loss journey?

What about with how fast you are making progress?

What happens when you start to go entertain those thoughts?

…from my experience, falling off track is right around the corner. You blink and you suddenly you are further than you ever planned on being.

When we struggle with these thoughts we have to take them captive. 
We have to submit them to Jesus.
We have to refuse to entertain them and give them life.

Here at Weightlosshero we battle these things together…because life is hard. Part of sanctification is facing new challenges and growing nearer to the Lord through them.

Sharing our addictive habits feels...scary…

As much as we like to think that we are open, honest, and 'authentic'...most of us don't want others to know the real us that struggles with addictive habits.

Years ago I would post on the internet and feel like such a fraud because I shared sooooo much of my life...

...but I didn't share my vaping habit...

...and I didn't share all the hangovers that would wipe me out...

...I never shared all the times I said I would never drink again and failed...

And when people would message me and say 'I just love you because you are so authentic'...I felt like such a fraud.

The reality is...I was a fraud.

As awful as that feels to say...it's true.

I was a fraud to EVERYONE in my life.

No one really knew the real me...and it ate me alive from the inside out.

There's a Bible verse that speaks to that in Psalm 32:3 when David says "For when I kept silent, my bones wasted away."

By God's grace I can now boast in my weakness.

I'm not afraid for those in my life to really know me.

And it's a beautiful thing.

You need others to help you through your battles in life...many of which will be fighting addictive habits.

Can I encourage you to join us on our upcoming Bible study (that starts Monday)?

Imagine being surrounded by hundreds of other women who are in this fight with you?

Imagine being fully known...and having women in the fight with you?

That's exactly what we are trying to accomplish by bringing so many women together and teaching the truth of God's Word.

I pray that throughout this process God helps you boast in your weaknesses, too.

It's the most freeing thing in the world.

If you want to join, comment the word ‘STUDY’ and we'll send over all the info!

Today someone came up to us at church and asked Heath if the boy in the green shirt belonged to him because they look JUST alike. 😍

It’s so crazy how the Lord made His plans for our lives and would bring us 4 children that resembled us in so many ways.

This week we moved forward to pull the kids out of school and homeschool all four of them. This was not a decision that was easy to make, but we felt that it was a step of obedience to the Lord and that delayed obedience was disobedience.

Our first week went GREAT! I was blessed because the Lord washed me with so much peace to KNOW that educating my kids at home (and based on the Word of God) was the right thing for our family.

You guys have been SO awesome to provide so much advice and direction. We haven’t chosen a formal curriculum, yet, because right now we are trying to fill in the massive gaps in their learning.

Between their biological parents and foster homes the children, as a whole, have been moved around to multiple homes and missed much of their necessary education.

So you’ll find us doing lots of flash cards, reading, writing drills, and math practice to really cement in what they should know before we move into teaching them things that are new.

We love that you guys are still here with us for all parts of our journey. Some of you have been here from before when I was in corporate America and did single live with no kids and no pets and have stayed through the many works of God in my life…and for that, I am so thankful.

If you homeschool, comment below with what curriculum(s) you use, and why, because you never know how you might help another homeschooling family (or a family considering)!

We went on to adopt 4 of those little hearts and are officially their mom and dad. We would not hesitate for one moment to adopt all 9 of them right now and truly light up when we hear from them or their family.  We have been told no, been rejected, were overwhlemed with paperwork, heard the most horrible stories from these kids, had experiences that grew our faith, dealt with police, were part of an amber alert, and feared losing the kids to a corrupt system…all things we couldn’t share real-time.  BUT! We have also experienced love unimaginable, a million ‘God-only’ stories, and a new understanding of what it really means to be adopted by God.  We have gained friends along the way and have suffered great losses as one of those friends is now with Jesus.  When you are in the adoptive process you feel like you are in a constant state of ‘hurry up and wait’…but then you look back and can see God’s mighty hand in every single phone call, every single ‘no’, and every single victory.  We are thankful that we are adopted by God…and it is only out of an abundance of that thankfulness that we began to walk down such an uncertain path that has led us to the most wonderful of places.  We, also, love that you are on this journey with us…and can’t wait to see what God has in store for our future.
.

Note: any children in this post are either adopted by us, are not ‘formally’ placements (just kids we cared for, personally, on an extended basis) or have aged out and have given us permission to share them 🤍

Infertility. A battle you never would have imagined you would be in. A war that no one on the outside can really see. A monthly mindset to trust God in all things…even in the midst of disappointment. This week marks 3 years since we began trying to conceive.  5 years ago I would have told you I didn’t want kids and now I have 6! I feared being a Mom! I was terrified to fail! And yet…as God changed my heart, my desires changed along with it. We got married…I became a bonus Mom…and my desire to have biological children grew quickly.  A few months of trying passed by, and I rested on Google’s answer that ‘most people’ will conceive in 6 months, or so…  …but then 6 months passed

…then 1 year  …then 2 years  …it was starting to seem like our desires and God’s plan were not the same.  What we didn’t know is that this same desire to conceive would lead us to consider adoption…an adoption that would have, likely, never happened had we conceived a child early-on in our marriage.  What we didn’t know is that God had already hand-picked 6 wonderful children for us that I would never carry in my womb and never birth…but would feel as much ‘my own’ as I know kids could possibly be.  What we didn’t know is that God would even make it to where my newly adopted children would even resemble me in many ways…like a cherry on top.  This is where trusting in God’s plan over our own is the only way to stay at peace. When we focus on OUR wishes and OUR wants we will be miserable until we get them (and, often, even after we get what we want)!

But when we trust in the God who opens and closes the womb, we know that He will give us what we need…and if He doesn’t give it, we don’t need it and it is for our good and God’s glory!  3 years later…our desires have not changed. We would LOVE for the Lord to bless us by allowing us to conceive a child…but we can, also, look around at the 6 blessings that we already have and be so grateful that God had a plan that far exceeded ours.
